WEBVTT

00:01.835 --> 00:03.003
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

00:03.003 --> 00:03.837
CAN YOU WALK?

00:03.837 --> 00:06.006
I HAVE A KNIFE IN MY CHEST.

00:08.008 --> 00:09.743
NOW CAN YOU WALK?

00:09.743 --> 00:11.712
I THINK I KILLED MY MOTHER.

00:11.712 --> 00:12.713
‐DISPATCH.
‐NO.

00:12.713 --> 00:14.314
NO, NO. NO, NO.
‐SHH.

00:14.314 --> 00:15.982
Please, please, please don't.
Please, please, please.

00:15.982 --> 00:18.685
JEFFERY, IF I WANTED YOU BUSTED,
YOU'D BE GONE ALREADY.

00:18.685 --> 00:19.686
YOU HERE TO I. D. HIM?

00:19.686 --> 00:20.887
David: YES.

00:20.887 --> 00:23.056
HE'S BREATHING.
CALL AN AMBULANCE.

00:23.056 --> 00:24.257
HE'S BREATHING.

00:24.257 --> 00:25.659
Candace: JEFFERY.
WHERE ARE YOU?

00:25.659 --> 00:29.162
JEFFERY: With Officer Justin,
standing in your backyard.

00:29.162 --> 00:30.597
WHAT?!

00:31.598 --> 00:34.635
[ INSECTS CHIRPING ]

00:38.171 --> 00:39.506
YOU KNOW WHAT?

00:39.506 --> 00:40.907
WHAT?

00:40.907 --> 00:43.644
ON SECOND THOUGHT,
MAYBE WE SHOULD WAIT OUTSIDE.

00:43.644 --> 00:44.978
SHE WOULD WANT
TO TALK TO ME.

00:44.978 --> 00:47.848
YEAH,
I DON'T ‐‐ I DON'T KNOW.

00:47.848 --> 00:49.616
WOULD YOU GET HER,
PLEASE?

00:49.616 --> 00:51.985
WHAT IS THIS ABOUT?

00:51.985 --> 00:55.989
WITH ALL DUE RESPECT,
I NEED TO SEE MRS. CRYER.

00:55.989 --> 00:57.357
SHE'S RESTING.

00:57.357 --> 01:00.060
I GET THAT,
BUT YOU LET US IN,

01:00.060 --> 01:01.835
AND THIS IS IMPORTANT.

01:03.970 --> 01:06.039
MS. SALLISON, YOU GONNA
HAVE TO TELL ME SOMETHING

01:06.039 --> 01:07.440
IF YOU WANT ME
TO GO GET HER.

01:09.042 --> 01:10.911
I GET IT.
YOU DON'T WANT TO LOSE YOUR JOB.

01:10.911 --> 01:13.146
NO, THAT'S NOT IT.

01:13.146 --> 01:14.781
I'M SURPRISED
YOU STILL WORK HERE.

01:14.781 --> 01:15.782
I DON'T.

01:15.782 --> 01:18.384
THEN WHAT'S ALL OF THIS?

01:18.384 --> 01:20.020
LOOKING OUT FOR A FRIEND.

01:20.020 --> 01:22.523
WHO COVERED UP THE HIT‐AND‐RUN
OF YOUR SON?

01:25.592 --> 01:27.060
MS. SALLISON,
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

01:27.060 --> 01:29.630
TO SPEAK TO MRS. CRYER.

01:29.630 --> 01:32.398
AGAIN, CAN I TELL HER
WHAT THIS IS ABOUT?

01:33.934 --> 01:35.836
WE NEED TO TALK TO HER
ABOUT WYATT.

01:35.836 --> 01:37.037
[ SCOFFS ]

01:37.037 --> 01:40.240
SHE CAN'T TAKE
ANYTHING ELSE TONIGHT.

01:40.240 --> 01:43.209
SHE JUST ASKED ME TO LEAVE
SO SHE CAN LAY DOWN.

01:43.209 --> 01:45.478
SHE WOULD WANT TO HEAR
WHAT I HAVE TO SAY.

01:45.478 --> 01:47.147
YEAH.

01:47.147 --> 01:50.083
SHE IS IN NO MOOD
TO TALK TO ANYONE,

01:50.083 --> 01:51.251
ESPECIALLY YOU.

01:51.251 --> 01:53.854
I'M SURE, BUT SHE WOULD WANT
TO HEAR <i>THIS.</i>

01:53.854 --> 01:57.257
YEAH,
YOU WOULD BE WRONG.

01:57.257 --> 02:00.060
WOULD YOU GET HER,
PLEASE?

02:00.060 --> 02:01.502
OKAY.

02:01.502 --> 02:02.669
BUT I WARNED YOU.

02:05.305 --> 02:06.873
HANNA.

02:06.873 --> 02:07.974
YES?

02:07.974 --> 02:10.076
WHY WAS THERE
AN AMBULANCE HERE?

02:10.076 --> 02:11.244
THERE WAS AN ACCIDENT HERE.

02:11.244 --> 02:12.312
WHAT HAPPENED?

02:12.312 --> 02:13.947
YOU NEED TO ASK
THE OWNER OF THIS HOUSE.

02:13.947 --> 02:15.982
‐I WILL.
‐OKAY.

02:15.982 --> 02:18.017
STAY RIGHT HERE.

02:18.017 --> 02:19.819
OKAY.
THANK YOU.

02:19.819 --> 02:21.988
I MEAN, RIGHT HERE.

02:21.988 --> 02:23.256
I HEARD YOU.

02:29.796 --> 02:33.634
♪♪♪♪

02:33.634 --> 02:36.637
‐‐Captions by VITAC‐‐
www.vitac.com

02:36.637 --> 02:39.506
CAPTIONS PAID FOR BY
DISCOVERY COMMUNICATIONS

02:43.777 --> 02:47.380
♪♪♪♪

02:47.380 --> 02:48.649
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

02:48.649 --> 02:49.850
[ DOOR OPENS ]

02:53.754 --> 02:55.989
MRS. CRYER.

02:55.989 --> 02:57.824
I THOUGHT
YOU WERE GOING HOME.

02:57.824 --> 02:59.793
I WAS ON MY WAY.

03:00.767 --> 03:02.435
BUT YOU'RE STILL HERE.

03:02.435 --> 03:04.938
I'M NOT LAUGHING.

03:07.941 --> 03:10.577
I'M NOT IN THE MOOD
FOR THIS, HANNA.

03:10.577 --> 03:13.213
I KNOW, AND I'M SORRY.

03:14.815 --> 03:15.816
THEN WHAT IS IT?

03:15.816 --> 03:17.117
[ SCOFFS ]

03:17.117 --> 03:19.686
SOMETHING ELSE IS GOING ON.

03:19.686 --> 03:20.721
WHAT?

03:23.489 --> 03:25.926
YOU NEED TO COME DOWNSTAIRS.

03:25.926 --> 03:27.661
HANNA.

03:27.661 --> 03:29.162
SOMEBODY WANTS
TO TALK TO YOU.

03:29.162 --> 03:31.331
WHO?

03:31.331 --> 03:33.634
I THINK YOU JUST NEED
TO COME SEE FOR YOURSELF.

03:35.101 --> 03:37.403
[ SIGHS ]

03:37.403 --> 03:38.605
WHO IS IT?

03:38.605 --> 03:41.141
COME ON.

03:41.141 --> 03:43.910
HANNA, I AM NOT IN THE MOOD
FOR ANY OF THIS RIGHT NOW.

03:43.910 --> 03:46.179
I KNOW.
I TOLD HER.

03:47.347 --> 03:48.515
"HER," WHO?

03:50.651 --> 03:51.652
THE D. A.

03:51.652 --> 03:55.188
‐WHAT?
‐YES.

03:57.423 --> 03:59.726
HERE, IN MY HOUSE?

03:59.726 --> 04:01.334
YEP.

04:01.334 --> 04:04.538
♪♪♪♪

04:08.975 --> 04:12.445
YOU HAVE THE AUDACITY
TO COME INTO MY HOME?

04:12.445 --> 04:14.515
HAVE YOU LOST
WHAT LITTLE BRAIN YOU HAD?

04:14.515 --> 04:15.582
‐MA'AM, MA'AM.
‐ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

04:15.582 --> 04:17.350
MRS. CRYER.
YOU NEED TO HEAR ‐‐

04:17.350 --> 04:19.853
GOOD, YOU BROUGHT
JUST ONE OFFICER WITH YOU.

04:19.853 --> 04:21.187
SIR, MAY I HAVE YOUR GUN?

04:21.187 --> 04:22.523
MA'AM?

04:22.523 --> 04:25.225
I'M GONNA SHOOT THIS BITCH
RIGHT BETWEEN THE EYES.

04:25.225 --> 04:27.027
MA'AM,
IT IS A FEDERAL OFFENSE

04:27.027 --> 04:28.294
TO THREATEN
AN OFFICER OF THE COURT.

04:28.294 --> 04:29.262
I DON'T GIVE A DAMN.

04:29.262 --> 04:30.997
SHE IS THE REASON
MY SON IS DEAD.

04:32.899 --> 04:34.233
MRS. CRYER, CALM DOWN.

04:34.233 --> 04:35.268
NO.

04:36.770 --> 04:39.573
IF YOU DO NOT GIVE ME A GUN,
THEN I WILL GET ONE,

04:39.573 --> 04:42.909
I PROMISE YOU,
AND I WILL SHOOT HER MYSELF.

04:42.909 --> 04:45.078
MRS. CRYER, I UNDERSTAND
THAT YOU'RE UPSET,

04:45.078 --> 04:47.280
BUT YOU REALLY NEED TO HEAR
WHAT I HAVE TO SAY.

04:47.280 --> 04:50.817
I DON'T GIVE A DAMN
WHAT YOU HAVE TO SAY.

04:50.817 --> 04:53.053
YOU WOULD WANT
TO HEAR THIS.

04:53.053 --> 04:54.521
UNLESS YOU ARE HERE
TO TELL ME

04:54.521 --> 04:56.823
THAT MY SON
IS BACK FROM THE DEAD,

04:56.823 --> 04:59.092
THEN YOU HAVE NOTHING
TO SAY TO ME.

04:59.760 --> 05:00.767
HE IS.

05:00.767 --> 05:02.536
‐WHAT?
‐WHAT?

05:03.570 --> 05:04.571
[ SIGHS ]

05:04.571 --> 05:07.307
HE IS, SO TO SPEAK.

05:07.307 --> 05:09.009
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

05:11.244 --> 05:12.713
HE WASN'T DEAD.

05:12.713 --> 05:14.380
WHAT?

05:14.380 --> 05:17.851
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING,
JENNIFER?

05:17.851 --> 05:21.087
HE WAS UNCONSCIOUS
FOR 32 HOURS.

05:21.087 --> 05:23.256
HE HAD O. D.'d.

05:23.256 --> 05:24.891
AND HIS BREATHING
WAS SO SHALLOW,

05:24.891 --> 05:26.993
AND HIS PULSE
WAS SO FAINT,

05:26.993 --> 05:28.962
THAT THE RESPONDING OFFICERS
WHO CAME THERE

05:28.962 --> 05:32.599
THOUGHT THAT HE WAS DEAD
WHEN THEY ARRIVED.

05:32.599 --> 05:34.300
MS. SALLISON, WHAT?

05:35.936 --> 05:40.473
WHAT KIND OF IDIOTS
DO YOU HAVE WORKING FOR YOU?

05:40.473 --> 05:42.743
BELIEVE IT OR NOT,
THIS HAS HAPPENED BEFORE.

05:42.743 --> 05:45.779
AND SO THAT JUST
MAKES IT OKAY?!

05:45.779 --> 05:47.981
I APOLOGIZE FOR THE DEPARTMENT
THAT'S HANDLING THIS,

05:47.981 --> 05:49.983
BUT THE GOOD NEWS IS
YOUR SON IS ALIVE,

05:49.983 --> 05:52.352
AND HE'S IN THE HOSPITAL,
BEING LOOKED AFTER.

05:52.352 --> 05:54.187
HOW IS HE?

05:54.187 --> 05:56.690
HE'S IN A MEDICALLY‐INDUCED
COMA ‐‐ THAT'S ALL WE KNOW.

05:56.690 --> 05:58.659
BUT THERE'S
A POLICE ESCORT OUTSIDE,

05:58.659 --> 06:00.567
READY TO TAKE YOU
TO THE HOSPITAL.

06:03.469 --> 06:06.940
YOU TAKE THAT ESCORT
AND YOU DRIVE IT UP YOUR ASS.

06:06.940 --> 06:09.475
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

06:09.475 --> 06:14.881
I WILL NOT GO
TO ANY DAMN HOSPITAL.

06:14.881 --> 06:18.151
I WILL NOT SEE MY SON
IN THAT WAY.

06:18.151 --> 06:20.353
‐MRS. CRYER.
‐NO.

06:21.888 --> 06:25.892
I WILL NOT SEE MY SON
LYING THERE IN THAT STATE.

06:25.892 --> 06:28.895
YOU WILL BRING HIM
BACK TO MY HOME

06:28.895 --> 06:31.364
THE WAY YOU FOUND HIM,

06:31.364 --> 06:37.671
BEFORE YOU PUMPED $12 MILLION
UP HIS NOSE AND IN HIS ARM.

06:37.671 --> 06:39.773
YOU, JENNIFER SALLISON,

06:39.773 --> 06:43.577
WILL RETURN HIM EXACTLY
THE WAY YOU FOUND HIM ‐‐

06:43.577 --> 06:46.513
WALKING AND TALKING.

06:46.513 --> 06:52.786
ANGRY AS HELL,
BUT FULL OF LIFE.

06:52.786 --> 06:58.324
AND UNTIL YOU DO THAT,
YOU ARE MY ENEMY.

06:58.324 --> 07:00.794
YOU NEED TO BE VERY CAREFUL
WHAT YOU SAY TO ME

07:00.794 --> 07:03.870
IN FRONT OF A ROOM
FULL OF WITNESSES.

07:03.870 --> 07:05.906
GET OUT OF MY HOUSE,
BITCH.

07:07.574 --> 07:09.175
NOW!

07:13.013 --> 07:16.049
♪♪♪♪

07:26.527 --> 07:28.061
[ BREATHES SHAKILY ]

07:29.129 --> 07:30.864
MRS. CRYER.

07:32.365 --> 07:34.267
MRS. CRYER.

07:34.267 --> 07:36.770
YOU REALLY NOT GONNA
GO DOWN AND SEE HIM?

07:36.770 --> 07:38.772
I CAN'T.
I CAN'T.

07:38.772 --> 07:40.574
I CAN'T SEE HIM
LIKE THAT.

07:40.574 --> 07:41.842
I CAN'T.
[ SOBS ]

07:41.842 --> 07:44.945
WHA‐‐ WHAT IF
HE DOESN'T MAKE IT?

07:44.945 --> 07:46.947
MRS. CRYER,
THIS IS YOUR SON.

07:46.947 --> 07:48.549
[ SNIFFLES ]

07:48.549 --> 07:50.450
I CAN'T.

07:50.450 --> 07:51.818
WELL...

07:51.818 --> 07:56.356
YOU TOLD ME NOT TO LOOK
AT AMANDA IN THAT BODY BAG.

07:56.356 --> 08:02.435
AND NOW MY LAST IMAGE OF HER
IS HER IN THAT BAG.

08:02.435 --> 08:07.908
I WILL NOT HAVE
MY LAST IMAGE OF MY SON...

08:07.908 --> 08:11.344
IN A HOSPITAL,
HOOKED UP TO TUBES.

08:14.515 --> 08:16.583
I WON'T.

08:16.583 --> 08:19.085
OKAY.

08:19.085 --> 08:22.022
NOW THAT YOU PUT IT THAT WAY,
I GET IT.

08:22.022 --> 08:23.423
I GET IT.
[ SNIFFLING ]

08:23.423 --> 08:25.926
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.

08:25.926 --> 08:27.894
I DON'T KNOW.

08:29.429 --> 08:31.197
I CAN'T GO THERE
AND SEE HIM.

08:33.600 --> 08:35.536
I CAN'T.

08:35.536 --> 08:37.270
DO YOU MIND IF I GO?

08:39.673 --> 08:41.474
I WAS HOPING
YOU WOULD SAY THAT.

08:44.010 --> 08:45.712
OKAY.

08:45.712 --> 08:46.913
OKAY, I WILL.

08:46.913 --> 08:48.481
THANK YOU.

08:50.483 --> 08:51.852
THANK YOU.

08:51.852 --> 08:53.887
[ SOBBING ]

08:58.358 --> 09:01.535
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

09:01.535 --> 09:03.537
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

09:03.537 --> 09:06.306
[ Ringing ]

09:06.306 --> 09:08.174
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

09:08.174 --> 09:10.343
‐HI.
‐Hey.

09:10.343 --> 09:12.613
DID YOU GET IT ALL
TAKEN CARE OF?

09:12.613 --> 09:13.880
YES.

09:13.880 --> 09:15.281
OKAY, GOOD.

09:15.281 --> 09:16.917
THANKS
FOR CHECKING ON ME.

09:16.917 --> 09:18.084
Yeah, I was.

09:18.084 --> 09:20.353
BUT THAT'S NOT THE ONLY REASON
WHY I'M CALLING.

09:20.353 --> 09:22.022
WHAT'S GOING ON?

09:22.022 --> 09:24.024
CAN YOU SEND ME A PICTURE
OF OSCAR RIGHT NOW?

09:24.024 --> 09:26.059
YEAH.

09:26.059 --> 09:30.330
I THINK I HAVE ONE OF US
FROM NEW YORK CITY.

09:30.330 --> 09:31.331
OKAY, SEND IT.

09:31.331 --> 09:33.734
HOLD ON.

09:33.734 --> 09:36.570
[ CELLPHONE DINGS ]

09:36.570 --> 09:38.171
THERE IT IS.

09:38.171 --> 09:39.773
You won't believe this.
‐WHAT?

09:39.773 --> 09:42.543
I'M LOOKING AT HIM.

09:42.543 --> 09:44.010
What?

09:44.010 --> 09:45.879
‐YEP.
‐WHERE ARE YOU?

09:45.879 --> 09:48.048
I'M AT SHAWN QUINTON'S.

09:48.048 --> 09:49.449
Here in Savannah?

09:49.449 --> 09:50.350
YEAH.

09:50.350 --> 09:52.085
‐HE'S HERE?
‐Yep.

09:52.085 --> 09:53.353
I'M ON MY WAY.

09:53.353 --> 09:55.221
OKAY,
BUT YOU BETTER HURRY.

09:55.221 --> 09:56.289
Keep him there.

09:56.289 --> 09:58.859
I CAN'T.
GRAYSON'S COMING.

09:58.859 --> 09:59.860
ERICA.

09:59.860 --> 10:00.867
[ SIGHS ]

10:00.867 --> 10:02.368
CANDACE, YOU KNOW GRAYSON.

10:02.368 --> 10:05.071
YOU KNOW THAT THIS IS
IMPORTANT, ERICA.

10:05.071 --> 10:07.874
YEAH, I KNOW.
GOT YOU FOR MILLIONS, BUT...

10:07.874 --> 10:10.376
IF I WORK GRAYSON RIGHT,
THIS COULD BE MILLIONS, TOO.

10:10.376 --> 10:11.745
PLEASE.

10:11.745 --> 10:13.346
LISTEN, I'LL DO
THE BEST THAT I CAN.

10:13.346 --> 10:15.115
OKAY.

10:15.115 --> 10:17.050
JUST DON'T ‐‐ DON'T TAKE
YOUR EYES OFF OF HIM.

10:17.050 --> 10:20.053
I'LL DO MY BEST.

10:22.022 --> 10:23.790
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

10:24.925 --> 10:27.961
[ JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING ]

10:31.832 --> 10:33.266
HI.

10:33.266 --> 10:34.901
HI.

10:34.901 --> 10:38.639
CAN I GET A, UM,
COSMO, PLEASE?

10:42.776 --> 10:45.078
YOU'RE NOT FROM AROUND HERE,
ARE YOU?

10:45.078 --> 10:48.481
NO, I'M NOT.

10:48.481 --> 10:49.850
IN TOWN LONG?

10:49.850 --> 10:52.485
NO.
JUST, UH, IN AND OUT.

10:52.485 --> 10:55.221
MM.

10:55.221 --> 10:56.757
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GO OUT
SOMETIME?

10:58.525 --> 11:00.326
[ SCOFFS ]

11:00.326 --> 11:02.703
EXCUSE ME?

11:02.703 --> 11:04.705
YOU AND I.

11:04.705 --> 11:07.874
NO.
I‐I DON'T THINK SO.

11:09.375 --> 11:13.279
[ CHUCKLES ]
NO? WHY?

11:13.279 --> 11:16.449
DO YOU NOT SEE THE WOMAN
I'M SITTING WITH?

11:18.985 --> 11:21.054
OH, I'M SORRY.
YOU'RE ON A DATE.

11:21.054 --> 11:23.023
YEAH.

11:24.625 --> 11:25.992
‐SORRY.
‐IT'S ALL RIGHT.

11:25.992 --> 11:28.161
DO ‐‐ DO YOU MIND
EXCUSING US, PLEASE?

11:28.161 --> 11:29.730
OH, NO.

11:29.730 --> 11:31.297
THANK YOU.

11:31.297 --> 11:32.699
‐[ CLEARS THROAT ]
‐I'M SORRY ABOUT THAT.

11:39.072 --> 11:41.107
SORRY, AGAIN.
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:41.107 --> 11:44.144
♪♪♪♪

11:59.125 --> 12:00.534
HI.

12:06.172 --> 12:09.075
♪♪♪♪

12:09.075 --> 12:11.111
[ ENGINE REVS ]

12:13.680 --> 12:14.681
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

12:14.681 --> 12:17.283
[ Ringing ]

12:17.283 --> 12:19.686
[ CHUCKLES ]
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

12:22.155 --> 12:24.758
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

12:24.758 --> 12:26.392
HI, CANDACE.

12:26.392 --> 12:29.495
YEAH, I'M SITTING HERE
WITH GRAYSON.

12:29.495 --> 12:32.098
I'm not gonna be able to drop
that bathing suit off to you.

12:33.534 --> 12:35.001
[ SMACKS LIPS ]
IS HE LEAVING?

12:35.001 --> 12:37.270
YEAH.

12:40.507 --> 12:42.208
DAMN IT.

12:42.208 --> 12:43.944
SORRY.

12:43.944 --> 12:45.245
NOTHING YOU CAN DO?

12:45.245 --> 12:46.547
No.

12:47.280 --> 12:50.116
YEAH, I MIGHT BE ABLE
TO CHECK THE CAR.

12:50.116 --> 12:52.886
DO ‐‐ DO YOU MIND
IF SHE PICKS IT UP, HONEY?

12:52.886 --> 12:56.957
HE DOESN'T MIND.
JUST, UM, ASK THE VALET FOR IT.

12:56.957 --> 12:58.391
OKAY.

12:58.391 --> 13:01.067
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.
SHE SAYS HI, BY THE WAY.

13:04.170 --> 13:05.271
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

13:10.611 --> 13:12.646
[ ENGINE REVS ]

13:18.585 --> 13:19.986
SORRY.

13:19.986 --> 13:22.322
I GUESS I'M NOT THE ONLY ONE
WITH A DATE TONIGHT, THOUGH.

13:22.322 --> 13:25.626
A GIRL CAN TRY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:25.626 --> 13:27.293
EXCUSE ME.

13:29.530 --> 13:30.997
HEY.

13:30.997 --> 13:33.166
YOU SEE THAT MAN BEHIND ME
IN A BLACK SUIT?

13:33.166 --> 13:35.702
DON'T BE SO OBVIOUS.

13:35.702 --> 13:37.738
I NEED YOU TO PUT THIS
UNDER HIS SEAT.

13:37.738 --> 13:40.507
AND WHEN I COME OUT,
HE CAN'T KNOW IT'S THERE.

13:40.507 --> 13:41.508
GOT IT?

13:41.508 --> 13:44.545
YES, MA'AM.
I GOT IT.

13:44.545 --> 13:46.379
WHAT IS IT?

13:46.379 --> 13:48.749
IT'S A PHONE, HONEY.

13:48.749 --> 13:50.784
JUST DO IT.

13:50.784 --> 13:52.318
MY EYES ARE UP HERE, HON.

13:52.318 --> 13:53.353
I GOT YOU.

13:58.892 --> 14:00.493
WHAT'S GOING ON?

14:00.493 --> 14:02.068
I THINK I GOT A PLAN.

14:02.068 --> 14:03.403
WHAT?

14:03.403 --> 14:04.705
YEAH, I'LL HAVE
TO CALL YOU LATER.

14:04.705 --> 14:06.172
GRAYSON'S WAITING
AT THE TABLE.

14:06.172 --> 14:07.674
UGH.
SO DISGUSTING.

14:07.674 --> 14:09.776
OKAY.

14:09.776 --> 14:10.877
DAMN IT.

14:10.877 --> 14:12.679
DON'T WORRY.

14:12.679 --> 14:14.648
OKAY.

14:16.583 --> 14:18.218
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

14:18.218 --> 14:19.953
NOT WORRIED.

14:22.623 --> 14:25.659
♪♪♪♪

14:44.410 --> 14:47.447
♪♪♪♪

14:56.189 --> 14:58.291
JEFFERY?

14:58.291 --> 15:00.066
‐HI.
‐HI.

15:02.302 --> 15:04.838
YOU KNOW JUSTIN.

15:09.475 --> 15:11.545
JUSTIN'S
A POLICE OFFICER.

15:13.346 --> 15:14.781
HI.

15:14.781 --> 15:17.417
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

15:24.157 --> 15:25.559
WHAT'S GOING ON?

15:29.830 --> 15:32.232
I TOLD HIM WHAT I DID.

15:38.271 --> 15:39.673
COME INSIDE.

15:41.407 --> 15:43.577
I'M GOING TO JAIL.

15:45.078 --> 15:47.548
JUSTIN, YOU CAN LEAVE NOW.

15:47.548 --> 15:49.382
‐NO, I CAN'T.
‐YES, YOU CAN.

15:49.382 --> 15:50.416
HE CAN'T.

15:53.253 --> 15:54.420
WHY?

15:57.123 --> 16:00.133
HE'S WRITING OUT
SOME INFORMATION FOR ME.

16:01.802 --> 16:03.670
ABOUT?

16:08.374 --> 16:10.476
MY MOTHER.

16:13.246 --> 16:14.314
FOR?

16:16.917 --> 16:18.652
HE KNOWS.

16:23.289 --> 16:25.692
WHAT EXACTLY DOES HE KNOW?

16:25.692 --> 16:29.129
♪♪♪♪

16:34.635 --> 16:36.770
THAT...

16:36.770 --> 16:38.138
I STABBED HER.

16:40.641 --> 16:42.308
I CHECKED
ON A POSSIBLE WARRANT.

16:42.308 --> 16:43.744
HE DOESN'T HAVE ONE.

16:46.680 --> 16:48.448
WHY ARE YOU <i>HERE?</i>

16:48.448 --> 16:51.818
RADIO WORKS BETTER OUT HERE.
HOUSE IS MADE OF CONCRETE.

16:51.818 --> 16:52.886
IT'S BUILT WELL.

16:57.290 --> 16:58.925
KNOWING MY MOTHER,

16:58.925 --> 17:02.703
SHE'S PROBABLY SENT
THE POLICE HERE FOR ME.

17:02.703 --> 17:05.105
MAYBE YOU SHOULD'VE STAYED
AT THE HOTEL, IN THE ROOM,

17:05.105 --> 17:06.472
SO SHE COULDN'T FIND YOU.

17:06.472 --> 17:07.874
IT'S TIME.

17:10.243 --> 17:12.879
IT'S TIME
WE GIVE ALL THIS UP.

17:12.879 --> 17:16.016
JEFFERY, RELAX.
OKAY?

17:16.016 --> 17:17.884
ARE YOU SURE
IT WAS THAT BAD?

17:22.589 --> 17:24.858
I BURIED A KNIFE
IN HER CHEST.

17:30.597 --> 17:31.598
WHO ARE YOU CALLING?

17:31.598 --> 17:33.634
UM...

17:33.634 --> 17:35.035
GIVE ME A MINUTE, OKAY?

17:42.576 --> 17:45.045
[ EXHALES ]

17:46.079 --> 17:48.114
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

17:52.452 --> 17:53.620
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

17:53.620 --> 17:54.454
HELLO?

17:54.454 --> 17:56.322
‐HEY.
‐Hey.

17:56.322 --> 17:57.658
DID YOU
FIND OUT ANYTHING?

17:57.658 --> 17:58.592
OH, SHE WOULDN'T
TELL ME NOTHING.

17:58.592 --> 18:00.260
[ SIGHS ]
OKAY.

18:00.260 --> 18:02.102
Where are you?

18:02.102 --> 18:03.469
AT HOME.

18:03.469 --> 18:04.671
WE MAY HAVE A PROBLEM.

18:04.671 --> 18:06.707
WHAT?

18:06.707 --> 18:08.642
JEFFERY IS HERE
WITH A COP.

18:08.642 --> 18:10.476
‐WHAT?
‐Yeah.

18:10.476 --> 18:11.978
They're in the backyard.

18:11.978 --> 18:13.780
‐WHAT?
‐MM‐HMM.

18:13.780 --> 18:17.618
YEAH, UM, HIS MOTHER
KNOWS ABOUT THE PACKAGE,

18:17.618 --> 18:19.953
so I need to find out
what's going on.

18:19.953 --> 18:20.954
CANDACE, LEAVE.

18:20.954 --> 18:22.088
NO. NOT YET.

18:22.088 --> 18:23.389
CANDACE, LEAVE NOW!

18:23.389 --> 18:24.858
I NEED TO FIND OUT
WHAT'S GOING ON.

18:24.858 --> 18:25.692
CANDACE!

18:25.692 --> 18:27.260
I WILL CALL YOU BACK.

18:27.260 --> 18:28.128
WHAT ARE YOU ‐‐
[ Click ]

18:28.128 --> 18:31.197
HELLO? CA‐‐

18:31.197 --> 18:32.332
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

18:35.368 --> 18:37.203
WHO WAS THAT?

18:37.203 --> 18:41.141
JUST A CONTACT I HAVE
AT THE HOSPITAL.

18:41.141 --> 18:42.643
WHAT DID THEY SAY?

18:42.643 --> 18:44.110
SHE WORKS FOR MERCY.

18:44.110 --> 18:46.780
UM, THEY DIDN'T
BRING YOUR MOTHER IN.

18:46.780 --> 18:48.414
THERE'S NO WORD.

18:51.718 --> 18:53.520
CAN YOU PLEASE
CALL THIS IN?

18:53.520 --> 18:56.422
JEFFERY,
CAN I...TALK TO YOU?

18:58.992 --> 19:00.634
YEAH.

19:00.634 --> 19:01.868
NOT HERE.

19:03.604 --> 19:04.638
COME ON.

19:08.675 --> 19:11.712
♪♪♪♪

19:18.451 --> 19:20.186
WHY IS HE HERE?

19:20.186 --> 19:23.323
WHAT, ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
I DON'T KNOW WHERE TO GO.

19:23.323 --> 19:26.026
BUT WHY DID YOU
BRING HIM HERE?

19:26.026 --> 19:27.594
DID YOU TELL HIM?

19:27.594 --> 19:28.895
NO, I DIDN'T TELL HIM.

19:28.895 --> 19:30.664
THEN WHY ARE YOU
IN THE BACKYARD WITH HIM?

19:30.664 --> 19:31.998
HE IS A COP.

19:31.998 --> 19:34.400
BECAUSE MY MOTHER IS GONNA
BRING THE POLICE HERE.

19:34.400 --> 19:36.236
SO, I‐I DON'T KNOW.

19:36.236 --> 19:37.270
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I WAS THINKING.

19:37.270 --> 19:38.872
GET RID OF HIM NOW.

19:41.608 --> 19:45.178
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO TOLD ME
TO GET TO KNOW HIM, CANDACE.

19:45.178 --> 19:47.714
NOT TO TELL HIM
YOUR STUFF.

19:47.714 --> 19:50.216
LET ME TELL YOU
HOW THIS WORKS.

19:50.216 --> 19:53.854
YOU GET HIS INFO,
HIS WEAKNESSES.

19:53.854 --> 19:55.055
YOU DON'T GIVE UP YOURS.

19:55.055 --> 19:56.823
[ SIGHS ]

19:56.823 --> 19:59.560
DO YOU KNOW HIS WEAKNESSES?

19:59.560 --> 20:02.503
A FEW.

20:02.503 --> 20:04.738
ARE YOU USING THEM?

20:04.738 --> 20:06.172
I, UH, THINK SO.

20:06.172 --> 20:07.641
HOW MUCH
DOES HE KNOW ABOUT YOU?

20:07.641 --> 20:08.642
MY FULL NAME.

20:08.642 --> 20:10.410
OH, JEFFERY.

20:10.410 --> 20:11.477
THAT'S TOO MUCH.

20:13.980 --> 20:16.116
WELL, I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.
I MEAN...

20:16.116 --> 20:18.652
GET HIS ASS
OUT OF HERE NOW.

20:25.626 --> 20:28.529
♪♪♪♪

20:33.066 --> 20:35.001
SHE'S NOT DEAD.

20:36.503 --> 20:37.804
THANK GOD.

20:37.804 --> 20:39.506
REALLY, JEFFERY?

20:39.506 --> 20:42.242
WOULD YOU ‐‐ STOP.
OKAY, THAT'S MY MOM.

20:42.242 --> 20:45.579
[ SCOFFS ] WELL, IF YOU
HADN'T REALLY DID WHAT YOU ‐‐

20:45.579 --> 20:49.950
HEY, STOP. PLEASE?
OKAY, I GOT ANGRY.

20:49.950 --> 20:53.186
AND I STILL DON'T KNOW
WHY I GET SO ANGRY, SO...

20:53.186 --> 20:55.989
YOU JUST ANSWERED
YOUR OWN QUESTION.

20:55.989 --> 20:57.624
WHAT?

20:57.624 --> 20:59.159
IT'S YOUR MOM.

21:00.460 --> 21:02.235
WHERE IS SHE?

21:02.235 --> 21:03.336
AMBULANCE.

21:03.336 --> 21:04.370
IS SHE OKAY?

21:04.370 --> 21:05.739
YEAH,
SHE'S GONNA BE FINE.

21:05.739 --> 21:06.740
DAMN.

21:06.740 --> 21:08.742
STOP.

21:08.742 --> 21:09.943
SORRY.

21:09.943 --> 21:12.679
THIS MEANS SHE'S GONNA
BE COMING FOR ME.

21:12.679 --> 21:16.316
W‐WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

21:16.316 --> 21:17.518
IT MEANS NOTHING.

21:17.518 --> 21:18.985
THANK YOU, JUSTIN.
YOU CAN GO NOW.

21:18.985 --> 21:20.687
NO, YOU KNOW WHAT?

21:20.687 --> 21:24.357
I DON'T ‐‐ I DON'T
WANT HIM TO GO.

21:24.357 --> 21:25.358
HE HAS TO.

21:25.358 --> 21:26.359
NO, CANDACE.

21:26.359 --> 21:29.262
NO. OKAY?
THERE'S TOO MUCH GOING ON,

21:29.262 --> 21:31.197
WITH THE WHOLE
WYATT SITUATION.

21:31.197 --> 21:34.601
I JUST ‐‐ I WANT HIM
HERE WITH ME, OKAY?

21:34.601 --> 21:37.604
JEFFERY,
HE'S A POLICE OFFICER.

21:37.604 --> 21:39.372
HE'S MY FRIEND.

21:39.372 --> 21:43.376
DON'T MISTAKE ME DOING MY JOB
AS FRIENDS, MR. HARRINGTON.

21:43.376 --> 21:45.411
YES, THAT WOULD
BE A MISTAKE.

21:49.115 --> 21:50.651
I'M GONNA GO HOME.

21:51.484 --> 21:54.354
LET HIM GO.

22:00.026 --> 22:01.602
OKAY.
[ DOOR OPENS ]

22:01.602 --> 22:04.070
WE NEED TO GET OUT OF HERE.
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

22:04.070 --> 22:07.708
IF SHE WAS GONNA SEND THE COPS,
SHE WOULD HAVE DONE IT BY NOW.

22:07.708 --> 22:10.276
SO, THEN WHAT ‐‐
WHAT IS SHE WAITING FOR?

22:12.579 --> 22:15.015
WHY DOES A SNAKE
WAIT TO STRIKE?

22:19.085 --> 22:21.054
TIMING.

22:21.054 --> 22:24.725
YEAH, WHAT TIMING?

22:24.725 --> 22:27.427
I DON'T KNOW.

22:27.427 --> 22:29.329
BUT I'M SURE WE'LL FIND OUT.

22:32.699 --> 22:35.001
I CAN'T DO THIS.
THIS IS ALL TOO MUCH.

22:35.001 --> 22:38.038
♪♪♪♪

22:41.642 --> 22:43.677
[ INSECTS CHIRPING ]

22:51.117 --> 22:52.152
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

22:52.152 --> 22:53.286
HANNA.

22:53.286 --> 22:54.855
HI.

22:56.690 --> 22:58.191
IS KATHERYN WITH YOU?

22:58.191 --> 23:01.301
SHE'S NOT COMING.

23:03.369 --> 23:05.071
WHY?

23:05.071 --> 23:07.473
SHE CAN'T HANDLE IT.

23:07.473 --> 23:09.943
SHE CAN'T HANDLE IT?
THIS IS HER SON.

23:09.943 --> 23:11.211
WHERE IS SHE?

23:11.211 --> 23:13.514
YOU NEED TO TALK TO HER
ABOUT THAT.

23:13.514 --> 23:14.981
I JUST CAME DOWN HERE
'CAUSE I TOLD HER

23:14.981 --> 23:17.551
I WOULD TELL HER
WHAT'S GOING ON.

23:17.551 --> 23:19.853
HE'S STABLE.

23:19.853 --> 23:21.454
THE DOCTOR WILL BE BACK
IN A FEW MINUTES

23:21.454 --> 23:23.456
WITH TEST RESULTS.

23:27.928 --> 23:29.429
HOW ARE YOU?

23:30.564 --> 23:31.765
HOW'S YOUR WIFE?

23:31.765 --> 23:33.534
YEAH.

23:33.534 --> 23:35.068
YOU MIGHT WANT
TO CHECK ON HER.

23:38.539 --> 23:39.606
DOCTOR.
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

23:39.606 --> 23:42.008
THIS IS,
UH, HANNA YOUNG.

23:42.008 --> 23:44.410
SHE'S HERE ON BEHALF
OF WYATT'S MOTHER.

23:44.410 --> 23:46.212
YOU CAN FILL HER IN
AS WELL.

23:46.212 --> 23:47.948
‐HI.
‐HI.

23:47.948 --> 23:49.816
HOW IS HE?

23:49.816 --> 23:52.218
WELL, HE SEEMS OKAY,
CONSIDERING.

23:52.218 --> 23:53.554
CONSIDERING WHAT?

23:53.554 --> 23:56.122
THE DRUGS.

23:56.122 --> 24:01.502
OPIATES, COCAINE, MARIJUANA,
AMPHETAMINES, ALCOHOL.

24:01.502 --> 24:04.070
LORD.

24:04.070 --> 24:06.940
HE WAS TRYING
TO KILL HIMSELF.

24:06.940 --> 24:08.742
THERE ARE BETTER WAYS
TO DO IT.

24:11.545 --> 24:13.213
WHY IS HE SO OUT OF IT?

24:13.213 --> 24:15.348
BECAUSE OF ALL THE MEDICATION
WE GAVE HIM.

24:17.684 --> 24:19.520
MY SON WAS IN A COMA.

24:21.688 --> 24:24.457
LOOKED LIKE THAT.

24:24.457 --> 24:26.226
IS HE IN ONE?

24:26.226 --> 24:29.029
HE WAS IN
A MEDICALLY‐INDUCED COMA.

24:29.029 --> 24:30.196
HE WAS HAVING SEIZURES

24:30.196 --> 24:32.733
BECAUSE OF ALL THE DRUGS
IN HIS SYSTEM,

24:32.733 --> 24:35.936
BUT HE'S STABLE NOW.

24:35.936 --> 24:37.437
ANY BRAIN DAMAGE?

24:37.437 --> 24:39.940
NO. HE NEVER HAD
A LOSS OF OXYGEN.

24:39.940 --> 24:41.708
HE HAD SHALLOW BREATHING,

24:41.708 --> 24:43.677
BUT HE DOESN'T EVEN NEED
A RESPIRATOR.

24:43.677 --> 24:45.078
HE'S BREATHING FINE
ON HIS OWN.

24:45.078 --> 24:46.813
OKAY, SO WHEN
WILL HE BE BETTER?

24:46.813 --> 24:49.482
WELL, WE JUST NEED TO WATCH
THE BRAIN ACTIVITY

24:49.482 --> 24:51.718
AND THE SEIZURES,
AND SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

24:51.718 --> 24:53.253
IT'S A WAITING GAME.
‐MM.

24:53.253 --> 24:56.322
THE NEXT 48 HOURS
WILL TELL IT ALL.

24:56.322 --> 24:57.357
OKAY.

24:57.357 --> 24:59.225
THANK YOU, DOCTOR.

25:03.103 --> 25:05.271
YOU LET KATHERYN KNOW
WHAT'S GOING ON.

25:05.271 --> 25:07.941
[ DOOR CLOSES ]
I'LL LET JIM KNOW.

25:07.941 --> 25:09.710
OKAY, I WILL.

25:09.710 --> 25:11.645
YEAH, YOU LET JIM KNOW.

25:14.748 --> 25:16.783
[ <i>INDISTINCT CHATTER</i>
<i>OVER P. A.</i> ]

25:18.985 --> 25:20.521
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

25:23.657 --> 25:25.992
UH, MRS. CRYER?
HI.

25:25.992 --> 25:27.794
I JUST SPOKE WITH THE DOCTOR,
AND HE SAID...

25:27.794 --> 25:29.830
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

25:29.830 --> 25:31.832
I TOLD YOU THAT
I DON'T HAVE IMPLANTS.

25:31.832 --> 25:33.366
MA'AM,
I'M LOOKING AT THE X‐RAY.

25:33.366 --> 25:34.968
WELL, THE X‐RAY IS WRONG.

25:34.968 --> 25:38.004
OKAY, UM...

25:38.004 --> 25:39.940
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
THERE'S NO DAMAGE HERE,

25:39.940 --> 25:43.510
JUST A LITTLE STITCHING,
BUT, UH, THE IMPLANT ‐‐

25:43.510 --> 25:46.146
I SAID I DIDN'T HAVE IMPLANTS!
CAN YOU HEAR?

25:46.146 --> 25:47.313
ALL RIGHT.
THE BREAST HAS RUPTURED.

25:47.313 --> 25:49.583
[ EXHALES ]
WILL I ‐‐ WILL I HAVE A SCAR?

25:49.583 --> 25:51.885
I DON'T WANT A SCAR.

25:51.885 --> 25:54.087
I DON'T WANT A SCAR.

25:54.087 --> 25:55.989
I WILL NOT LEAVE HERE
WITH A SCAR.

25:55.989 --> 25:59.392
THIS BODY HAS NO SCARS.

25:59.392 --> 26:03.136
I HAD A CHILD, AND I HAVE
NO STRETCH MARKS, NO NOTHING,

26:03.136 --> 26:05.939
AND I WILL NOT
HAVE ONE TODAY.

26:05.939 --> 26:08.542
DO YOU KNOW WHAT
A MALPRACTICE LAWSUIT IS?

26:08.542 --> 26:09.543
IF THERE'S A SCAR ‐‐

26:09.543 --> 26:10.977
SIR, UH,
YOU CAN'T BE IN HERE.

26:12.579 --> 26:14.681
I'M HER HUSBAND.

26:16.249 --> 26:18.084
DAVID.

26:19.686 --> 26:21.922
SO, WHAT HAPPENED?

26:21.922 --> 26:24.558
LEAVE US.

26:24.558 --> 26:28.128
MA'AM, WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE
OF STITCHING.

26:28.128 --> 26:29.663
ONCE THE ANESTHESIA
WEARS OFF,

26:29.663 --> 26:31.264
YOU'RE GONNA BE
IN A LOT OF PAIN.

26:31.264 --> 26:32.633
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:32.633 --> 26:34.835
TELL ME SOMETHING NEW.

26:34.835 --> 26:36.970
NOW, I SAID, LEAVE US.

26:36.970 --> 26:38.839
GET YOUR ASS OUT OF HERE,
PLEASE.

26:40.106 --> 26:42.408
[ SIGHS ]

26:47.447 --> 26:51.251
SO, WHAT HAPPENED?

26:51.251 --> 26:53.186
JEFFERY HAPPENED.

26:53.186 --> 26:55.088
HE STABBED ME.

26:55.088 --> 26:56.890
WHAT?

26:56.890 --> 26:59.960
YOU HEARD ME.

26:59.960 --> 27:02.168
‐JEFFERY?
‐I DON'T KNOW.

27:02.168 --> 27:05.005
UNLESS YOU HAVE ANOTHER SON
THAT I DON'T KNOW ABOUT.

27:05.005 --> 27:07.674
[ SIGHS ]

27:07.674 --> 27:10.711
JEFFERY STABBED YOU.

27:10.711 --> 27:12.412
YES, HE DID.

27:12.412 --> 27:14.347
HUH.

27:14.347 --> 27:16.316
WHAT IS "HUH"?

27:16.316 --> 27:18.985
BOBBY SAFEMAN.

27:18.985 --> 27:22.222
WHAT THE HELL DOES THAT HAVE
TO DO WITH ANYTHING, DAVID?

27:22.222 --> 27:25.125
YOU DON'T REMEMBER
BOBBY SAFEMAN?

27:25.125 --> 27:26.827
WHAT ABOUT IT?

27:26.827 --> 27:29.663
[ SCOFFS ]

27:29.663 --> 27:33.099
WELL, STARTING WHEN ‐‐ WHEN
JEFFERY WAS ABOUT SIX YEARS OLD,

27:33.099 --> 27:37.504
THAT BOY BOBBY
BULLIED AND PUSHED

27:37.504 --> 27:41.642
AND HARASSED HIM FOR YEARS,
'TILL HE WAS 11.

27:41.642 --> 27:43.109
JEFFERY NEVER TOLD US.

27:43.109 --> 27:46.046
TEACHERS TOLD US,
PRINCIPALS TOLD US,

27:46.046 --> 27:47.614
JEFFERY NEVER SAID A WORD.

27:47.614 --> 27:51.151
EVEN WHEN I ASKED HIM,
HE WOULD SAY, "I'M JUST FINE."

27:51.151 --> 27:58.091
JUST LET IT BUILD UP INSIDE,
LET IT BUILD UP AND FESTER.

27:58.091 --> 28:01.227
HE TOOK IT IN.

28:01.227 --> 28:04.971
THEN, ONE DAY, THEY WERE
AT A LITTLE‐LEAGUE PRACTICE

28:04.971 --> 28:07.974
AND BOBBY SAID
ONE THING TOO MANY,

28:07.974 --> 28:10.143
AND JEFFERY TOOK UP
A BASEBALL BAT

28:10.143 --> 28:12.779
AND BEAT THAT BOY
INTO A COMA.

28:14.948 --> 28:17.150
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU DON'T REMEMBER THAT.

28:19.920 --> 28:24.758
YOU DEFENDED AGAINST THE LAWSUIT
THAT BOBBY'S PARENTS FILED.

28:27.027 --> 28:28.361
I'M HIS MOTHER.

28:28.361 --> 28:33.066
NO, YOU'RE JUST
ANOTHER BOBBY SAFEMAN.

28:33.066 --> 28:34.200
AND YOU BETTER BE GLAD

28:34.200 --> 28:36.537
THAT JEFFERY DIDN'T HAVE
A BASEBALL BAT.

28:39.573 --> 28:41.908
NOW, YOU TELL THAT DOCTOR
YOU HAVE IMPLANTS

28:41.908 --> 28:44.711
SO HE CAN SAFE YOUR LIFE.

28:44.711 --> 28:47.180
TOXINS IN YOUR BLOOD SYSTEM
WILL KILL YOU.

28:52.352 --> 28:56.122
ON SECOND THOUGHT...

28:56.122 --> 28:57.524
DON'T TELL HIM.

29:03.336 --> 29:04.237
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

29:09.375 --> 29:10.677
[ VEHICLE APPROACHES ]

29:10.677 --> 29:13.714
♪♪♪♪

29:31.998 --> 29:34.000
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

29:34.000 --> 29:36.870
WHO?

29:36.870 --> 29:39.339
WHO IS IT?
‐BENNY.

29:40.641 --> 29:41.942
‐YO.
‐HEY.

29:41.942 --> 29:43.276
WHAT THE HELL?

29:43.276 --> 29:45.679
‐WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
‐YOU DIDN'T CALL ME BACK.

29:45.679 --> 29:47.548
UM, IT'S FINE.

29:47.548 --> 29:48.815
IT'S FINE.
DID HE TELL HIM?

29:48.815 --> 29:49.816
NO.

29:49.816 --> 29:51.151
WHERE IS HE?

29:51.151 --> 29:53.887
HE'S UPSTAIRS,
LAYING DOWN.

29:53.887 --> 29:55.055
IS HE COOL?

29:55.055 --> 29:56.022
NO.

29:56.022 --> 29:57.090
ALL RIGHT,
LET ME TALK TO HIM.

29:57.090 --> 29:58.424
NO ‐‐ UNH‐UNH.

29:58.424 --> 29:59.726
CANDACE, I WANT
TO TALK TO HIM.

29:59.726 --> 30:00.627
WHY?

30:00.627 --> 30:03.036
'CAUSE I WANT
TO TALK TO HIM.

30:03.036 --> 30:05.338
BENNY, HE DOESN'T KNOW
YOU HELPED ME.

30:05.338 --> 30:07.608
OKAY.

30:07.608 --> 30:08.575
WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA SAY TO HIM?

30:08.575 --> 30:10.010
CANDACE, I'M GONNA ‐‐

30:10.010 --> 30:12.278
NO. NO.

30:12.278 --> 30:13.246
YOU WILL SPOOK HIM.

30:13.246 --> 30:14.581
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

30:14.581 --> 30:16.182
WHO IS IT?

30:16.182 --> 30:18.985
ERICA.

30:18.985 --> 30:20.320
COME IN.

30:20.320 --> 30:21.454
[ DOOR OPENS ]

30:27.694 --> 30:29.362
HI.

30:29.362 --> 30:30.731
HEY.

30:30.731 --> 30:32.999
ERICA?

30:32.999 --> 30:35.702
BENNY.

30:35.702 --> 30:37.303
